                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1693" notAfter="1847">
                        <p>Likely rebound in India, Tight-backed in polished red artificially-grained
                              goatskin <material>leather</material> over
                              <material>pasteboards</material> (Type III binding without flap as per
                           Déroche). Machine-made endbands adhered at head and tail. European
                           spotted <material>marbled paper</material> pastedowns and made flyleaves,
                           with antique spot <material>marbled paper</material> hinges and subsequent 
                           <material>wove paper</material> flyleaves.</p> 
                           <decoNote type="binding"><p>Board edges ruled with decorative roll featuring alternating
                              dots and diamonds. Spine paletted with rows
                           small quatrefoils in <material>gold</material>, with the title handwritten in
                           nasta‘liq script in black <material>black</material> on a
                              <material>paper</material> label.</p></decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
